Author: kaviarormonroe
Content:
Well there are two big strands of leftcom whenever someone mentions it, Bukharinites, the italian left (bordigist), the german-dutch left (the councilists), the Damenites, and the french/anarchist strand (Communization)

Council Communists like Mattick, Pannekoek, certain German and Dutch communist parties, are the ones who disagree with Lenin on a number of things (I dont really like to call them leftcoms because it makes the term completely ambiguous with another completely separate tendency)

Italian Left Communism are people like Bordiga, Damen, etc, orgs like IntCP and ICT.
Leftcom covers both but they are not at all the same, or even similar.
also Bukharin? many on the Italian Left like Bukharin's stuff before Lenin's death, after his death, there is a lot if divergence on a multitude of things like SIOC.
Italian Left is Leninist, not in the ML/Stalinist falsification of the term, in that, what advancements Lenin did make, what contributions he had, we recognize as being properly Marxist
big oversimplification, byeah
